OS:
	Linux
	Windows 10

DEPENDENCIES:
	Python3
	Crypto++
	MySQL
	Lua

GIT REPO INCLUDES (LINUX users may ignore):
		libcrypto.a
		Crypto++ header files
		
		mysqlcppconn8-static.lib
		Mysqlcppconn8 header files

		Boost header files

		liblua.a 
		Lua header files
	
SETUP:
	1. Install g++ if not installed
	2. Install Crypto++
	3. Install MySQL-Connector-8
	4. Install Boost Libraries
	5. Install Lua


INSTALLING G++:
	Linux: Open terminal and run command 'sudo apt install g++'
	
	Windows:
	
INSTALLING CRYPTO++:
	Linux: Open terminal and run command 'sudo apt install libcrypto++-dev libcrypto++-doc libcrypto++-utils'
	
	Windows: a. If running on 32-bit system, download Crypto++ source and build the lib in Visual Studio. Replace lib/libcryptopp.a with newly build 32-bit version
		 b. If running on 64-bit system, the 64-bit lib and source is already included
	
INSTALLING MYSQL-CONNECTOR:
	Linux: Open terminal and run 'sudo apt install libmysqlcppconn-dev'
	
	Windows: Required headers and library already in Aurorasrc

INSTALLING BOOST LIBRARIES:
	Linux: Open terminal and run command 'sudo apt install libboost-all-dev'

	Windows: Required headers and library already in AuroraSrc


INSTALLING LUA:
	Linux: Open terminal and navigate to Desktop or Downloads.
	       Run commands:
			'curl -R -O http://www.lua.org/ftp/lua-5.3.5.tar.gz'
			'tar zxf lua-5.3.5.tar.gz'
			'cd lua-5.3.5'
			'make linux test'
			'sudo make install'
		If there are errors during the install it's likely due to missing dependencies. Ex: readline
		If that is the case install missing dependencies. Ex: 'sudo apt install libreadline-dev'

	Windows: Required headers and library already in AuroraSrc
